You said:
what is a tool interaction
ChatGPT said:
A “tool interaction” is when I use one of the built-in helper systems that isn’t just me typing words back to you.

Examples in plain English:

Web browsing/search (pulling live sources)

Reading or searching files you uploaded (like your .docx)

Creating/reading calendar or email items (if connected)

Generating images

Running code to produce a file (PDF, spreadsheet, etc.)

Automations/reminders

Anything that calls an external or specialized subsystem

In this chat, the big one is: I read and analyzed your uploaded Word documents using the file-reading/search tooling. That counts as a tool interaction.

Why that matters:
Some conversations get put into a mode where long-term memory saving is turned off after certain tool use. I don’t control that switch, and I don’t get to see the exact rule that triggered it—just the result that memory is disabled for this thread.

