- Provide a resources/stylesheets/pdf.scss (or equivalent) with:
  - Clean typography
  - Page breaks between major sections
  - Header/footer with title + page numbers
- Use only freely available fonts or system fonts by default. Do NOT add proprietary fonts.

VALIDATION SCRIPT REQUIREMENTS:
- scripts/validate_golden_rule.py reads curriculum_data/golden_rule_hours.yaml
- Validates:
  - Every bucket has hours_total.
  - If a bucket has subunits, sum(subunits) == hours_total.
  - Sum(core buckets excluding math) == 240.
  - Math == 40.
  - Total == 280.
- If validation fails, exit non-zero and print a clear error message.

GITHUB ACTIONS WORKFLOW REQUIREMENTS (pages.yml):
- On push to main and workflow_dispatch.
- Jobs:
  - build:
    - checkout
    - setup-python
    - pip install -r requirements.txt
    - install Playwright browsers/deps required by mkdocs-exporter (use python -m playwright install --with-deps chromium)
    - run validation script
    - mkdocs build --clean
    - upload artifact using actions/upload-pages-artifact (artifact path: site/)
  - deploy:
    - needs build
    - permissions: pages: write, id-token: write
    - deploy using actions/deploy-pages
- This should deploy to GitHub Pages via the official artifact workflow, not by pushing to gh-pages.

README REQUIREMENTS:
- Explain:
  - How to run locally
  - How PDFs are generated
  - How to add new curriculum content pages
  - Change control rules (PRs only)
  - Where the Golden Rule file lives and how it is enforced

CHANGELOG REQUIREMENTS:
- Add a template section for logging approved changes.

