ChatGPT said:
That message is GitHub warning you about renaming your default branch. Nothing is “broken” yet. You’ve got two ways to handle it depending on what you actually want.

What’s happening

Your repo default branch is NOT named main (it’s probably master or something else).

GitHub is nudging you to rename it to main.

If your Pages site is currently publishing from that branch, GitHub will temporarily unpublish it until Pages is pointed at the renamed branch and a commit exists on it.

Option A (recommended): Rename the branch and repoint Pages
Do this if you want the modern standard: default branch = main.

Rename the default branch in GitHub

Repo → Settings → Branches → Default branch → Rename

Rename whatever it is now (often master) to main

Fix GitHub Pages settings

Repo → Settings → Pages

Under “Build and deployment”

If it’s “Deploy from a branch”: set Branch to main and pick /root or /docs (whatever you use)

If it’s “GitHub Actions”: update the workflow if it hard-codes the old branch name (search your repo for master)

Make a tiny commit to trigger publish

Edit a README line and commit, or add a blank file. Pages should republish after that.

If you have collaborators using git locally, send them this (exactly)
They need to update their local branch name. If the old branch was master, this is the clean version:

git fetch origin
git checkout master
git branch -m master main
git branch -u origin/main main
git remote set-head origin -a
Option B: Don’t rename, just shut GitHub up
Do this if you don’t want any disruption right now.

Leave the branch name alone.

Make sure Pages is configured to deploy from the branch you already use.

Ignore the suggestion.

Why your Pages site “unpublishes”
Because GitHub Pages was pointing at the old branch name. When you rename it, that pointer breaks until you point Pages at the new branch.

Fast check (so you don’t guess)

Go to Settings → Pages and tell me what it says under:

“Source” / “Build and deployment”

“Branch” and “Folder”
Then I can tell you exactly what needs to be changed in your specific setup.

