Two points to tighten so you don’t get surprised later:

Playwright reality check
Your “no Playwright in requirements.txt” note is still compatible with “Playwright is used,” because it can be a transitive dependency (pulled in by a PDF/export plugin). But for reproducibility, decide which you want:

If Playwright is required for PDF export in CI: explicitly pin it (directly) or at least document that it’s a transitive dependency and that Chromium install is required.

If PDF export is optional: gate it behind a flag in the workflow so normal builds don’t depend on browser downloads.

CI vs Codespace
You proved PDF generation works in Codespace by installing Chromium + system libs. GitHub Actions may still fail if those libs aren’t present on the runner (depends on ubuntu image and what’s preinstalled). If the Pages workflow generates PDFs, make sure .github/workflows/pages.yml includes:

python -m playwright install chromium

any required system packages (or use a container / apt install step)

caching if you care about runtime

