ChatGPT said:

Thought for 1m 9s
Good. Your grep/ls output confirmed it: Copilot generated a full software-development curriculum skeleton and wired it into mkdocs.yml. That cannot go to main under ANEW branding. You already did the right thing removing the zip artifacts.

Now do the two surgical fixes that get you back on track.

1) Remove the software-curriculum placeholder content
Run:

git rm -r docs/curriculum
Then remove the corresponding nav section from mkdocs.yml (the lines you saw in grep around 101–114).

Fast way to find all nav entries that reference it:

grep -n "curriculum/" -n mkdocs.yml
Edit mkdocs.yml and delete every nav item pointing at curriculum/... (Developer Fundamentals, Programming Essentials, Web Development, Backend Development, Mathematics, etc.).

After that, confirm nothing is still pointing at it:

grep -Rni "curriculum/" mkdocs.yml docs || true
2) Fix the PDF-link warning (PR builds don’t generate the PDF)
Your warning is happening because mkdocs-pr.yml builds without producing downloads/curriculum.pdf, but docs/index.md links to it.

Fix: remove the clickable link and replace with plain text.

In docs/index.md, change any markdown like:

[Download the curriculum PDF](downloads/curriculum.pdf)
to plain text, for example:

Curriculum PDF is generated in production builds and published under downloads/curriculum.pdf.
That removes the warning in PR mode and avoids strict-mode failures later.

3) Rebuild and verify (both modes)
PR build (no PDF):

python -m mkdocs build -f mkdocs-pr.yml --clean
Main build (with PDF):

python -m mkdocs build --clean
ls -lh site/downloads/curriculum.pdf
Validation:

python scripts/validate_golden_rule.py
4) Commit + push
git add -A
git commit -m "Remove placeholder software curriculum and clean nav/PDF link"
git push
5) One last sanity scan (make sure “programming” isn’t anywhere public-facing)
grep -RniE "programming|web dev|backend|javascript|developer fundamentals" docs mkdocs.yml README.md || true
If you paste your mkdocs.yml nav: block after you delete the curriculum section, I’ll rewrite it into the clean structure you actually want (Governance + Professional Development + Shop Instruction placeholders aligned to your Golden Rule categories), without pointing to missing pages.

