Thought for 34s
Yep — this mkdocs.yml is still pointing at a whole bunch of files you already deleted (docs/curriculum/...). That’s exactly why MkDocs is screaming.

Do this in two clean cuts.

1) Replace your nav: block (delete the dead curriculum nav)
In mkdocs.yml, replace everything from nav: down to the last Grit/Instructor line with this:

nav:
  - Home: index.md

  - Governance:
      - Single Source of Truth: governance/single-source.md
      - Pull Request Workflow: governance/pr-workflow.md
      - Golden Rule Enforcement: governance/golden-rule.md
      - Change Control: governance/change-control.md
      - Governance Overview: governance/overview.md

  - Professional Development:
      - Grit & Growth Mindset: professional-development/grit-growth-mindset/index.md
      - Grit & Growth Mindset (Instructor): professional-development/grit-growth-mindset/instructor.md
That removes every reference to the deleted curriculum/... pages.

2) Kill the PDF link warning (so you can actually turn strict mode on)
Right now docs/index.md links to downloads/curriculum.pdf and MkDocs warns because that file isn’t in docs/ (it’s generated into site/).

Fix: change the link in docs/index.md to the published URL on GitHub Pages (MkDocs won’t try to validate it as an internal doc file):

Use this exact URL:

https://mandy1eigh007.github.io/curriculum_master/downloads/curriculum.pdf
Also add a note like “PDF is generated on main branch builds” since PR builds may not generate it.

Optional but matches your “no icons” rule
Remove these two blocks from mkdocs.yml:

Under theme: delete:

icon:
  repo: fontawesome/brands/github
Under extra: delete the whole social: section.

Then run the checks
python scripts/validate_golden_rule.py
python -m mkdocs build --clean
python -m mkdocs serve
If mkdocs build finishes with no warnings, flip:

strict: true
