# ANEW Curriculum Master

This repository is the single source of truth for curriculum content and Golden Rule hour enforcement.

## Governance

- Single Source of Truth
- Pull Request Workflow
- Golden Rule Enforcement
- Change Control
- Governance Overview

## Professional Development

- Grit & Growth Mindset (Student)
- Grit & Growth Mindset (Instructor)

## Curriculum PDF

The curriculum PDF is generated during production builds and published here:

https://mandy1eigh007.github.io/curriculum_master/downloads/curriculum.pdf
Now fix the one line in docs/governance/single-source.md where it claims there’s a curriculum folder. Replace that tree line with this:

├── professional-development/      # Professional development modules (student + instructor)
After those changes, run:

python scripts/validate_golden_rule.py
mkdocs build --clean
mkdocs serve
That should eliminate the broken-nav warnings and keep your repo aligned with the fact you intentionally nuked the placeholder software curriculum.

