ChatGPT said:

Thought for 6m 5s
Here’s the full fixed mkdocs.yml.

What it does (without drama):

Removes the deleted docs/curriculum/** pages from nav (so you stop getting those “not found” warnings).

Fixes the PDF stylesheet path so Playwright stops throwing net::ERR_FILE_NOT_FOUND.

Adds the official MkDocs Exporter PDF toggle env var so mkdocs serve doesn’t try to generate PDFs and blow up your dev loop. 

# MkDocs Configuration for ANEW Curriculum Master
# Docs-as-code curriculum repository with Golden Rule enforcement

site_name: ANEW Curriculum Master
site_description: Single source of truth for ANEW curriculum content
site_author: ANEW
site_url: https://mandy1eigh007.github.io/curriculum_master/

repo_name: mandy1eigh007/curriculum_master
repo_url: https://github.com/mandy1eigh007/curriculum_master
edit_uri: edit/main/docs/

copyright: Copyright &copy; 2026 ANEW

theme:
  name: material
  language: en
  palette:
    primary: blue
    accent: green
  font: false
  features:
    - navigation.tabs
    - navigation.sections
    - navigation.top
    - search.highlight
    - search.share
    - toc.follow

extra_css:
  - stylesheets/extra.css
  - styles/anew.css

plugins:
  - search
  - exporter:
      formats:
        pdf:
          # IMPORTANT:
          # - Set MKDOCS_EXPORTER_PDF_ENABLED=false for mkdocs serve (fast dev)
          # - Set MKDOCS_EXPORTER_PDF_ENABLED=true for mkdocs build (generate PDF)
          enabled: !ENV [MKDOCS_EXPORTER_PDF_ENABLED, false]  # default: OFF for dev
          concurrency: 1
          aggregator:
            enabled: true
            output: downloads/curriculum.pdf
            covers: none
          # This must be a path that exists in the built site.
          # Your file lives at: docs/stylesheets/pdf.css
          # MkDocs copies it to: site/stylesheets/pdf.css
          stylesheets:
            - stylesheets/pdf.css

markdown_extensions:
  - abbr
  - admonition
  - attr_list
  - def_list
  - footnotes
  - meta
  - md_in_html
  - tables
  - toc:
      permalink: false
      toc_depth: 3

  - pymdownx.arithmatex:
      generic: true
  - pymdownx.betterem:
      smart_enable: all
  - pymdownx.caret
  - pymdownx.details
  - pymdownx.highlight:
      anchor_linenums: true
      line_spans: __span
      pygments_lang_class: true
  - pymdownx.inlinehilite
  - pymdownx.keys
  - pymdownx.mark
  - pymdownx.smartsymbols
  - pymdownx.superfences
  - pymdownx.tabbed:
      alternate_style: true
  - pymdownx.tasklist:
      custom_checkbox: true
  - pymdownx.tilde

nav:
  - Home: index.md

  - Single Source of Truth: governance/single-source.md
  - Pull Request Workflow: governance/pr-workflow.md
  - Golden Rule Enforcement: governance/golden-rule.md
  - Change Control: governance/change-control.md
  - Governance Overview: governance/overview.md

  - Grit & Growth Mindset: professional-development/grit-growth-mindset/index.md
  - Grit & Growth Mindset (Instructor): professional-development/grit-growth-mindset/instructor.md

strict: false
use_directory_urls: true
Run commands (copy/paste exactly):

# Dev (no PDF generation, no Playwright pain)
MKDOCS_EXPORTER_PDF_ENABLED=false python -m mkdocs serve

# Production-style build (generates the combined PDF)
MKDOCS_EXPORTER_PDF_ENABLED=true python -m mkdocs build --clean
If Playwright hasn’t been installed in that Codespace image yet, this is the required install command per MkDocs Exporter docs: 

playwright install chrome --with-deps
